From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 05:48:06 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] katirun: handle make --help/-h; kati: JSONL trace records
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

--help/-h previously fell through to kati's flag parser and failed;
both make entries now print a GNU-shaped usage listing the supported
options. The upstream-style assignment trace (kept for rkati parity)
now emits self-contained JSONL lines tagged with the emitting make's
directory — concurrent in-process makes interleave at line granularity
instead of shredding a framed document, and a make that never touches
a traced variable emits nothing. The sarun-native path (assignments
recorded in the box DB, searchable in the UI) follows separately.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01B97aMMA3rHQW7gsyBB2Cpa
